                            <comment id="13123960" author="mgrigorov" created="Mon, 10 Oct 2011 09:06:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Your problem is that the StatelessForm uses POST by default.&lt;br/&gt;
If you override its&lt;br/&gt;
        @Override&lt;br/&gt;
	protected String getMethod()&lt;/p&gt;
	{
		return Form.METHOD_GET;
	}

&lt;p&gt;then the generated URL is: &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8080/stateless/foo?id1_hf_0=&amp;amp;0-1.IFormSubmitListener-statelessform=&amp;amp;textfield=10&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8080/stateless/foo?id1_hf_0=&amp;amp;0-1.IFormSubmitListener-statelessform=&amp;amp;textfield=10&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
and you can hit it as many times as you want.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13126750" author="chansen" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2011 17:44:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What I actually want is for the StatelessForm to use POST and &lt;b&gt;only&lt;/b&gt; POST because submitting a form via GET is often undesirable. Is this possible?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; Sorry for not being more clear about that originally.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13127670" author="mgrigorov" created="Fri, 14 Oct 2011 16:22:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The form submits with POST by default but it is not possible to copy/paste the URL and send it to another person in this case.&lt;br/&gt;
Read about &apos;redirect after post&apos; pattern.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13127680" author="chansen" created="Fri, 14 Oct 2011 16:39:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Martin, it is possible to copy/paste the URL and send it to another person in this case because the form can also be submitted via GET (despite a method of POST). Click on the links in the description for proof. Clicking on the link submits the form with all blank values.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I know about &apos;redirect after post&apos;, but it doesn&apos;t help in this case because a GET to the post-redirect URL will submit the form with all blank values.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13131230" author="ivaynberg" created="Thu, 20 Oct 2011 00:46:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;martin - there is no redirect after post for stateless forms :/&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i added Form#onMethodMismatch() callback that is invoked when a form is submitted with a method that doesnt match getMethod().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;stateful forms ignore the mismatch, while stateless forms&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;setResponsePage(getPage().getClass(), getPage().getPageParameters());
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which seems to be the only sane default.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if you dont want to wait for 1.5.3 it should be rather trivial to implement the same thing in a statelessform subclass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13131726" author="chansen" created="Thu, 20 Oct 2011 16:19:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That should work for me. Thanks for your help.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
